HONG KONG , September 28 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Garrison of the People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- stationed in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region -LRB- SAR -RRB- will open its barracks to the public on October 1 , the National Day .
Groups will be allowed to tour camps at Stanley and Stonecutters Island and visit gunboats , according to a statement issued by the garrison .
It will be the first time since Hong Kong 's return to the motherland on July 1 that local residents have been allowed inside the garrison 's military bases and also marks the first National Day celebrations by PLA forces in Hong Kong .
The garrison troops will stage cultural shows , basketball matches and other activities on their open day .
The two camps will be open between 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. in two sessions to receive up to 40 groups and organizations each including up to 50 people , the statement said .
It stressed that the open day is aimed at improving communications and understanding between the garrison troops and the general public .
`` There will be a morning and an afternoon session and we shall receive 20 groups at most in each session , '' a spokesman for the garrison told reporters this morning .
`` We think that it is good enough as the forces have only been stationed here for three months and there might not be too many things to see , '' he added .
